<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03143g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03143g">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03143g"> 143(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> M offers Lsd</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But the felons came up and said: &ldquo;King, harken to the counsel we give thee in all loyalty. The Queen was wrongfully slandered, we confess; but if she and Tristram return together to the court, there will be more evil talk. Let Tristram go away for a season; one day no doubt thou wilt recall him.&rdquo; Mark did so; he commanded Tristram by his barons to go without delay. Then Tristram approached the Queen, and bade her farewell. The Queen was ashamed because of the assembly, and she blushed. But the King was moved to pity, and speaking to his nephew for the first time, he said: &ldquo;Where wilt thou go in these rags? Take from my treasury all things needed for thee, <mark>gold and silver</mark>, and vair.&rdquo; <small> Joseph B&eacute;dier, <a name="JBLR1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JBLR1"><cite title="source">Le roman de Tristan et Iseut</cite></a> (1900) XI &lsquo;Le Gu&eacute; Aventureux&rsquo;, 127 [The Ford Perilous, 125]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
